The South African Weather Services says Cyclone Kenneth, which is expected to hit Tanzania and Mozambique this week, will not affect South Africa. Forecasters have predicted that Durbanites can expect a 30% chance of rain on Thursday. The city is currently reeling from a storm that has caused extensive loss of life and damage. Weather SA predicted a 30% chance of rain over the southern parts of the province and a sixty percent chance of rain over the north. The forecast is that from tomorrow, there will be no sight of rain at all. People living in areas that the storm affected more adversely, like Chatsworth, Malvern and Umlazi can expect relief from the rain in these areas. This as the death toll has currently exceeded 60, leaving more than one thousand displaced. Watch for more:   